The Umbral are shadow given permanent form — humanoids whose substance is as much darkness as flesh, whose origin lies in the world's deepest rupture between light and anti-light. Not demons, not undead, not evil: the living residue of the Black Sun Shard's most intense influence, people who dwelt in shadow-charged spaces where the Shard's anti-light leaks into the world, whose bodies over generations incorporated anti-light into cellular foundation. The Gloamvault beneath Midgaard is their most significant habitation site, but Umbral communities exist wherever Shard influence concentrates. Physical description: difficult to perceive clearly even in direct light — the eye slides off them slightly, as though not quite fully where they appear to be. In daylight: lean, pale-gray humanoids with very dark eyes (pupil and iris sometimes indistinguishable) and hair from deep charcoal to void-black. Skin has faintly iridescent quality — simultaneously present and absent. In low light, outlines soften; in shadow, extraordinarily difficult to see. Lighter than apparent size; physical impacts that should produce specific tactile feedback sometimes produce the sensation of pressing into something that gives unexpectedly. Heal slowly in direct sunlight; recover better in darkness or shadow. Stat profile: STR 10, INT 22, WIS 14, DEX 22, CON 16. Strong in Shadow and Mental; weak in Holy and Physical; resistant to Shadow and Mental; susceptible to Holy and Fire. Racial skills: sneak, mystical potency, enhanced critical. Sneak is passive, not learned: shadow-constituted nature makes them naturally difficult to perceive. The Gloamvault predates Midgaard's First Stone Accord — the archive was already old when Midgaard was built above it. The Umbral were there first. Principle of necessary absence: what is not present shapes reality as powerfully as what is. Shadow-archives maintained in near-total darkness using phosphorescent ink.

