Umbral communities in Midgaard's deep levels have existed for as long as the city has, and longer. The Gloamvault's shadow-archives contain records of the sealed warrants, Conclave transfers, and Ash-and-Iron administrative decisions that Continuity archivists have either deliberately omitted from or sealed in official records. The Reckoning faction has quietly cultivated Umbral archive relationships, recognizing that shadow-archives contain the sealed warrant evidence Continuity suppresses. The Continuity faction tolerates Umbral communities because their intelligence and legal discretion functions are genuinely useful — but also because suppression of Umbral communities has consistently failed. The city's surface inhabitants maintain a complex relationship: Umbral notaries, shadow-archivists, and intelligence gatherers are valuable; Umbral communities maintaining parallel record-keeping create awkward questions about which records are authoritative. Guard Command files Umbral community incidents under "deep district residents" with protocols that acknowledge practical non-suppression. The Lantern Registry's formal classification of Umbral is disputed between Continuity (which prefers classification that minimizes institutional disruption) and Reckoning (which argues accurate classification supports the broader transparency argument). The Gloamvault sits under Midgaard as permanent evidence that the Umbral were there first. This is not commemorated in any civic curriculum.

