Mafdet's attestation system creates a functional mechanism for Umbral civic standing without requiring anatomical classification that accommodates their semi-substantial nature. The Claw Mark Registry processes Umbral through conduct-based attestation: what has this person done, who has witnessed it, what are the terms of any attested commitments. The semi-substantial nature of Umbral bodies creates specific complications for the physical attestation process — the standard witnessed handclasp that Mafdet tradition uses to formalize attestation requires tactile confirmation that Umbral presence sometimes fails to provide clearly. The Swift Court has developed alternative attestation protocols for Umbral: formal declaration before three witnesses counts as attestation where physical contact is uncertain. The Quarantine Ledger's classification of shadow-associated materials includes Umbral-carried documents, which are technically shadow-archive format — legible only in near-total darkness with appropriate sensory adaptation. This creates a specific professional niche: Umbral archivists as custodians of documents that require specific handling protocols.

