An Umbral living in Midgaard's deep levels occupies the position that their philosophy most fully describes: necessary presence defined by institutional absence. The shadow-archives contain the actual record; the Gloamvault predates the city above it; the records that Continuity suppresses are accessible in the dark below. The institutional tension is not one that Umbral philosophy finds surprising or destabilizing — absence shapes reality as powerfully as presence, and the Continuity faction's sealed records produce an absence that defines the city's political landscape as certainly as any present document. The Reckoning faction cultivates Umbral archive access because the archives contain what the official record lacks. The Continuity faction tolerates this because suppression has consistently failed and Umbral intelligence function is genuinely useful. An Umbral in Midgaard is simultaneously the city's most valuable archival resource and its most persistent institutional inconvenience: their records prove the official records are incomplete, and their existence proves that the city cannot successfully suppress what exists in its own foundations. The city was built above the Gloamvault. The Umbral remain.

